I am currently working on a fairly involved plug-in to help JIRA integrate into various existing systems in the enterprise. I would like to be able to send emails that actually look like normal JIRA emails like ones that are typically sent through the notification system. 

The class https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/6.4.11/com/atlassian/jira/mail/builder/EmailBuilder.html looking at it's source seems to be exactly what I want. However, the developer kit and what not discourages use of things from the *jira-core* dependency which is where this class currently resides. In fact most of the email magic that JIRA does isn't in the API. I feel like as a developer  I am having to either depend on the jira-core and non @PublicAPI parts which doesn't appear to be a good idea for good reasons; or re-invent the wheel. 

I would love to be able to send emails using JIRA that actually already look like normal JIRA emails and use the *CSSInliner* class correct _which is not in JIRA API either_. It would be great to have this feature work within as well as without the context of something happening with an issue as well.

