- If you run the unattended install as root it creates duplicate jira users if the jira user already exist. The documentation [Unattended mode|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jira/installing-jira-on-linux-191501165.html#InstallingJIRAonLinux-PerforminganUnattendedInstallation] does mention to run the uninstaller which does delete the user so following this path it doesn't happen. However it would be nice if the script checked if the user exist instead of creating a new one.

